ai.summary: Marcham Jubilee Walks is a 13-kilometre moderate countryside hike in the United Kingdom. The route offers a pleasant mix of farmland, hedgerows, and village surroundings and can be completed in roughly 3–4 hours depending on pace and breaks.
ai.terrain_summary: Mixed terrain with tarmac country lanes, compact earth paths, and grassy tracks. Expect some uneven ground, gentle inclines, and gates or stiles; conditions vary with weather.
ai.safety_notes: Check the weather forecast before you go. Tell someone your planned route and estimated time. Bring a charged phone, map or GPS, and enough water. Wear sturdy footwear, dress in layers, and carry a lightweight rain jacket. Watch for livestock on farmland, mind gates and stiles, and keep dogs under control.
ai.best_seasons: Spring to early autumn (roughly March–October) for the best conditions; walkable year-round with appropriate gear.
